tk_spot_light:
### Tezos Delphi Upgrade 🚀🐳
A new Tezos upgrade is in preparation right now. This will likely be the biggest feature upgrade ever made on Tezos. We encourage all wallet and tooling providers to stay on top and use [Dalphanet](https://dalpha.tzstats.com). Read more about the upcoming changes in our [blog](https://blockwatch.cc/blog/tezos-delphi-v007-rc1-review/).
tk_spot_light_dalphanet:
### 🌱 This is Tezos D-alpha-net 🚧
Although features here have been pre-empted by the next Tezos protocol [v007](https://delphi.tzstats.com) (Delphi) we keep this explorer as an early tech preview on v008 release candidates. Explorer and API may break or reset without announcement. We encourage all wallet and infra providers to [read the docs](https://tezos.gitlab.io/api/rpc.html) and experiment!
tk_spot_light_delphinet:
### 🌱 This is Tezos Delphi Testnet 🚧
Use this network to test your integrations for the upcoming mainnet release in November 2020. RPC changes to Carthage should minimal, [read the docs](https://blog.nomadic-labs.com/delphi-official-release.html). Have fun and stay safe!
tk_spot_light_cartnet:
### 🌱 This is Tezos Carthagenet 🚧
A new testnet for [Tezos v007 Delphi](https://delphi.tzstats.com) is available. If the current [vote](https://tzstats.com/election/head) is accepted, the new protocol goes live on Tezos mainnet around November 12, 2020. Please help test the new protocol and migrate your development infrastructure early!
tk_spot_light_delphi:
### 🌱 Vote for Delphi Proposal 🚀
Other than announced before, Delphi is an interim proposal which improves gas costs and makes Tezos ready for DeFi! Read more [here](https://forum.tezosagora.org/t/delphi/2150/13) and [here](https://blog.nomadic-labs.com/delphi-official-release.html) and VOTE.
